The paper is about machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexity and intractability of neural machine translation (NMT) models, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a novel testing methodology, which falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential threats to personal safety due to inferior machine translation results, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of cybersecurity (cs.CY).
